WHAT THESE FILES ARE, AND ARE NOT, IN THIS HARNESS. They are the UPSTREAM's
stored reference numbers. They are NOT this harness's ground truth: the oracle
in eval/bench/analytic_fea.py computes every value from the stated closed form,
and these files are read only to CROSS-CHECK that computation against an
independent party. Where a stored number disagrees with the formula it cites,
the module says so with exact numbers rather than adopting it -- see the
cantilever_modal / column_buckling rounding notes and, materially, the two
fixed_fixed_* displacement rows, which upstream itself documents as coarse-mesh
solver goldens rather than closed-form references.
